parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission software can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to accelerate, leading to a safety risk, especially when merging or crossing intersections.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate when pressing the gas pedal
gets stuck at a specific speed (30-45 MPH)
and the RPMs get stuck at 3-4 thousand RPMs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning compressor can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a safety risk, especially when driving in heavy traffic or on the highway.
symptoms: The air conditioning compressor stops working
makes noise
and the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent power loss and stalling can cause the vehicle to lose speed and acceleration, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on high-speed roads. The failure can also lead to a loss of control and potentially cause a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle's power fluctuates
the vehicle stalls
the vehicle will not accelerate above a certain speed (e.g.
30 MPH)
the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the automatic braking system can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle comes to a hard stop without warning
the vehicle stops suddenly without any obstacles in front
the seatbelt tightens
and the body is thrown forward
causing discomfort or pain.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Failure to Accelerate
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and failure to accelerate can cause the vehicle to lose power and momentum, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the vehicle does not accelerate as needed
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle hesitates or struggles to move forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to emit excessive pollutants, leading to environmental harm and potentially causing respiratory issues for individuals with pre-existing conditions. Additionally, the failure can trigger the Check Engine light, which can lead to decreased fuel efficiency and engine performance.
symptoms: The Service Engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle emits excessive pollutants
decreased fuel efficiency
decreased engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning driver-side seatbelt can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The driver-side seatbelt does not lock or retract properly
the seatbelt warning light is illuminated
the seatbelt is stuck or jammed
the seatbelt buckle does not latch securely.
